Description: Lower body sherd of South Ionian pottery open vessel, perhaps a phiale or the like; interior glazed black; exterior glazed except for a reserved band at outside of underside; inscription cut on exterior.
Curator's comments: From a pot of the same kind as 1886,0401.947, or quite possibly from the same pot.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.936)
